If this article is typical of his writings on evolutionary theory,
it's not clear to me that he deserves much beyond blind abuse;
certainly he does not offer serious scientific challenges to
evolutionary theory, or even an interesting and logically consistent
_argumentum ad consequentiam_.  Of course, if only &quot;most&quot; of his
respondents offer either blind support or abuse, presumably he's
encountered, and ignored, more substantial replies.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; The answer to this has been implicit in what I have written.
&gt; Nevertheless, it is worth spelling out. It is because Darwinism has
&gt; embedded itself so deeply into the assumptions of our age, that it
